The paper deals with the computational complexity of functions and their evaluation mechanisms, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory. The use of memoization and sharing is a common technique in algorithm design and optimization, which suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). However, the paper also discusses the notion of ramified recurrence, which is a concept in implicit computational complexity, indicating that the paper may also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the mention of a "natural cost model" suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, and cs.PL, in that order.
